Definition: to a meager degree or in a meager manner
Example: these voices are meagerly represented at the conference; the area is slenderly endowed with natural resources
Synonyms: amply, adj, all, meager, sparingly, thrifty, sparing, slenderly, small, slender, meagrely, to, a, degree, or, in, manner, these, voices, are, represented, at, the, conference, area, is, endowed, with, natural, resources
Category: adv.all
